sql:
SELECT COUNT(bug_id) AS total_bugs
FROM bugs
WHERE project_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(bug_id) AS resolved_bugs_count
FROM bug_status
WHERE resolved_by_id = 1;

SELECT bug_id, description
FROM bugs
WHERE severity = 'Major';

SELECT COUNT(*) AS resolved_bug_count
FROM bugs
WHERE resolution_date IS NOT NULL;

SELECT name
FROM developers
WHERE developer_id IN (
  SELECT DISTINCT developer_id
  FROM bug_assignments
);

external_knowledge:
- Active projects refer to projects that are currently in progress; 
- Non-reopened bugs are those that have been resolved and not reopened for further work;
- Details of bugs include information about the bugs themselves, their assignments, and associated comments and attachments.

